<subSubSection id="C3610DBCEE00FFFFFE894137FEA763AE" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC45E37EE00FFFFFE894137FEA763AE" blockId="25.[264,1323,358,1577]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B90F8225EE00FFFFFE894137FE5D62EF" bold="true" box="[312,432,630,656]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Thorax (except scutellum) black in ground colour; posterior 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFB304136FB6162EE" box="[1153,1164,631,657]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFB264136FB4B62EE" box="[1175,1190,631,657]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
or more of the scutellum dark red. Abdomen black in ground colour, sides of the abdominal tergites 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFEB94186FEDE629E" box="[264,307,711,737]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
dark red or brown; abdomen very weakly microtrichose with dark blue reflections. Tibiae black or dark brown. Fifth abdominal tergite 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFCD541AEFC376376" box="[868,986,751,777]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="0.675" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.65">0.65–0.70</number>
times as long as tergite 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFB4341AEFAE96376" box="[1266,1284,751,777]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="4.0">4</number>
. ɗ: frons 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFEFD4056FE2D634E" box="[332,448,791,817]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="0.43000000000000005" valueMax="0.46" valueMin="0.4">0.40–0.46</number>
times as wide as an eye in dorsal view; postpedicel about twice as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation id="134042B2EE00FFFFFEDF407EFE5A6326" box="[366,439,831,857]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="12.[264,370,1736,1757]" captionTargetBox="[264,1308,290,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[260,1308,775,1723]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Pales spp. 1. Pales abdita sp. nov. paratype ɗ (Cyprus), habitus. 2. Pales marae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170908/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFE16407EFE5A6326" box="[423,439,831,857]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFD04407EFD296326" box="[693,708,831,857]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
without, 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFC87407EFCA86326" box="[822,837,831,857]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="4.0">4</number>
with very short and weak median discal setae. Ψ: frons 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFE094026FDC663FE" box="[440,555,871,897]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="0.73" valueMax="0.76" valueMin="0.7">0.70–0.76</number>
times as wide as an eye in dorsal view; postpedicel 2.0– 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFB0E4026FB0963FE" box="[1215,1252,871,897]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2.6">2.6</number>
times as long as pedicel; abdominal tergites 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFD6D40CEFD0663D6" box="[732,747,911,937]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number id="3DB34C10EE00FFFFFC9B40CEFCD463D6" box="[810,825,911,937]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="4.0">4</number>
with very weak and short median discal setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
